n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                    \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                    \n                        \n                                    \n\n\n\n\u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"custom_block_0\"\u003e\n\u003ch3\u003eKey Takeaways\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv\u003e \n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e Windows 11 24H2 update leaves undeletable files hogging 9GB of storage space \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e Normal methods can\u0026#39;t remove these files due to a bug with the new updating system \u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e Microsoft is aware of the issue and is working on a fix to address this problem. \u003c/li\u003e\n \u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHave you noticed that your Windows 11 machine has less free space on it after installing the 24H2 update? Don\u0026#39;t worry, you\u0026#39;re not going crazy. Reports are coming in that the update process leaves around 9GB of files sitting on your drive, and the worst bit is that you can\u0026#39;t just delete them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"e539-4993-a9caf19d10f1\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/windows-11-24h2/\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2400\" height=\"1600\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Text reading Windows 11 2024 Update over a blue background\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/windows-11-2024-update.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/windows-11-24h2/\" title=\"The Windows 11 2024 Update is now available — here\u0026#39;s what\u0026#39;s new and why it\u0026#39;s not Windows 12\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e The Windows 11 2024 Update is now available — here\u0026#39;s what\u0026#39;s new and why it\u0026#39;s not Windows 12 \u003c/a\u003e \u003c/h5\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe Windows 11 2024 Update will bring a ton of changes to the operating system, including better support for Arm devices.\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"windows-11-24h2-is-hogging-people-39-s-storage-space\"\u003e Windows 11 24H2 is hogging people\u0026#39;s storage space \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"6000\" height=\"4000\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A Windows 11 laptop showing the Focus sessions screen and FancyZones in PowerToys\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/windows-11-productivity-optimizations.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eAs spotted by \u003ca href=\"https://www.windowslatest.com/2024/10/10/windows-11-24h2-issue-creates-undeletable-8-63-gb-windows-update-cache/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eWindows Latest\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, people are reporting a strange bug where updating to Windows 11 24H2 leaves around 9GB of files sitting around on the PC\u0026#39;s drive, which are undeletable. These files can be found within the Windows Update cache, which is where the operating system stores everything it needs to carry out an update.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eUsually, these files are either deleted by Windows itself or by the user. In fact, the Disk Cleanup tool gives you the option to empty out the Windows Update cache folder and start anew. The only problem is, none of the usual methods for erasing the files seem to work. In the Feedback Hub, people are documenting their attempts, and none of them have seen success yet.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFortunately, Microsoft is aware of the issue and mentioned to \u003cem\u003eWindows Latest\u003c/em\u003e that it\u0026#39;s working on a fix. Turns out, the issue is due to teething problems with the new \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/explaining-checkpoint-updates-windows-11/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003echeckpoint updating system\u003c/a\u003e, which is meant to reduce the size of Windows updates. The system is tagging files as required for future updates, so it won\u0026#39;t let anything delete them. Seems that it kind of got the wrong idea as to what it was meant to be doing. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cem\u003eWindows Latest\u003c/em\u003e states that the files may not actually be 9GB large - they\u0026#39;re just incorrectly informing Windows that they are. Regardless, here\u0026#39;s hoping Microsoft gets a fix out the door soon.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n    \n        \n\n    \n\n        \n\n\n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                    \n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
